    AGA Clinical Practice Guideline on the Role of Biomarkers for the Management of Ulcerative Colitis. 
The panel also proposed key implementation considerations for optimal use of biomarkers, and identified areas for future research. In patients with UC, noninvasive biomarkers, including fecal calprotectin, fecal lactoferrin, and serum CRP can inform disease monitoring and management.
